						               													<description>Take on the investigative work in an exciting criminal case!&amp;#10;Follow the clues. Who has a motive? Are the alibis correct?&amp;#10;Excitement and fun with numerous hints. &amp;#10;For some of the research you need access to the internet.&amp;#10;You are forming a special commission to investigate a murder. The previous police investigations have not been successful.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The police headquarters finally needs progress, and therefore sent you the order to take over the investigation. With the order you will receive the investigation results found so far for the case in an envelope.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The group of potential perpetrators has already been narrowed down somewhat. Now your creativity and a sense of crime is required.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Work your way through the evidence and clues discovered so far, do research.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Do suspects have alibis and are out of the question for the crime? Who is the perpetrator?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Examine the various clues, discuss in the group what motives the suspects might have had to commit a murder. Who has something to hide?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It is best if your special commission consists of 2-7 players to determine together. The game can also be played solo.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You can be creative and use tools during the investigation. Research on the Internet may also be necessary to track down the perpetrator.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
